Set and Get Functions) Explain why a class might provide a set function and a get function
for a data member?

I've been told not to make my variables public inside a class. I should always make a get and a set function.
For example :
class Whatever
{

public:
	void setSentence(const std::string& str) { sentence = str; }
	void setAnInteger(const int integer) { anInteger = integer; }

	std::string getSentence() { return sentence; }
	int getAnInteger() { return anInteger; }

private:
	std::string sentence;
	int anInteger;

};
